1
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:06,632
PREVIOUSLY

2
00:00:07,382 --> 00:00:08,925
Hey, it's me, Uncle.

3
00:00:08,926 --> 00:00:10,260
Miss Jeong Jian?

4
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:13,388
Uh, Mr. Jeong Jinman has been found dead.

5
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:17,183
This is what my uncle sold?

6
00:00:17,184 --> 00:00:18,309
You being serious?

7
00:00:18,310 --> 00:00:19,311
THEN… IS JEONG JINMAN DEAD?

8
00:00:20,479 --> 00:00:21,771
THEN… YOU'LL DIE TODAY TOO,
JEONG JIAN?

9
00:00:29,655 --> 00:00:31,030
Wow!

10
00:00:31,031 --> 00:00:32,908
The veteran warriors
have all gathered together!

11
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:38,663
The first person who manages
to kill Jinman's niece

12
00:00:38,664 --> 00:00:39,872
or captures her alive

13
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:41,332
will bring home a big fat bonus.

14
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:42,918
All right, the rabbit hunt begins!

15
00:00:48,215 --> 00:00:50,132
Listen up, Jeong Jian.

16
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,467
Whatever scares you,

17
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:53,845
keep your eyes open and face it head-on.

18
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:57,348
I see that you don't think
before you act.

19
00:00:57,349 --> 00:00:59,100
That's not what your uncle would do.

20
00:00:59,101 --> 00:01:01,394
Yes, on the floor
where your uncle did most of his work

21
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:03,522
is a door that opens into Murthehelp.

22
00:01:04,940 --> 00:01:06,774
No way.

23
00:01:06,775 --> 00:01:07,901
It actually exists.

24
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,029
Wait, no, please, it's too bright.

25
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:14,073
You haven't answered my question yet!

26
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:15,199
Jeong Jian!

27
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,450
D-d-don't trust him!

28
00:01:17,536 --> 00:01:18,745
Jeongmin!

29
00:01:20,998 --> 00:01:23,208
But there is something
you should know.

30
00:01:23,834 --> 00:01:26,712
Your Uncle Jinman killed
a lot of people too.

31
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:29,714
You and I both get paid
to kill people.

32
00:01:29,715 --> 00:01:31,757
Stop pretending to be righteous.

33
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:32,925
It makes me sick.

34
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:35,304
In the end, you and I
are more alike than you think.

35
00:01:46,398 --> 00:01:47,940
If you don't kill me here,

36
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:49,400
I'll kill everyone.

37
00:01:49,401 --> 00:01:53,238
All your friends, and family, and anyone
who has anything to do with you.

38
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:56,283
You must be Jeong Jian.

39
00:01:57,075 --> 00:01:59,494
You really do take after your uncle.

40
00:02:05,459 --> 00:02:06,543
That you, Master?

41
00:02:07,044 --> 00:02:08,586
We don't have time, Jian.

42
00:02:08,587 --> 00:02:09,837
Bale's after you.

43
00:02:09,838 --> 00:02:11,422
You're up, you two.

44
00:02:11,423 --> 00:02:12,965
Go and handle this.

45
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:19,930
Hey there, twins.

46
00:02:19,931 --> 00:02:21,642
Today is the day we go to Hell.

47
00:02:35,447 --> 00:02:37,448
Jian, you better run!

48
00:02:37,449 --> 00:02:39,033
- Minhye!
- Get outta here!

49
00:02:42,496 --> 00:02:44,747
I'll give you two options
to choose from.

50
00:02:44,748 --> 00:02:47,834
But ultimately,
the choice is yours to make.

51
00:03:14,403 --> 00:03:15,820
It should be me…

52
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:19,616
who takes his life away.

53
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,161
Don't you think?

54
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:30,835
A SHOP FOR KILLERS 2

55
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,071
Team Leader?

56
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:06,538
What's going on?

57
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:19,801
It's the server room! Move, now!

58
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:26,076
A SHOP FOR KILLERS 2

59
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:35,710
EPISODE 01
JINMAN ON THE SAME DAY

60
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:11,788
Wait! Jeong Jinman!

61
00:06:12,414 --> 00:06:14,999
You have to let me down!

62
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,209
Hey, you fucker!

63
00:06:58,168 --> 00:07:00,210
Time of death is 1900 hours.

64
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:02,421
I've transferred the body
to the Hansarang Gyeongae Hospital

65
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:04,049
mortuary in Yecheong County.

66
00:07:05,216 --> 00:07:07,801
His niece Jeong Jian
is his only surviving family.

67
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:09,846
No need to involve Yecheong Police.

68
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:09,114
North Korean defector.

69
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:12,491
Can't believe you're still alive.

70
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:14,785
Well, that's because security
in South Korea's

71
00:08:14,786 --> 00:08:16,246
become soft since I've been gone.

72
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:18,247
Look at you.

73
00:08:18,248 --> 00:08:20,124
You don't look like
you've come across any guards.

74
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,208
Hey.

75
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:26,130
Officer Jinwoo.

76
00:08:26,131 --> 00:08:27,215
Pasin.

77
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:29,759
-  Jinwoo-krap.
-  How are you?

78
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:32,052
You're working out too much.

79
00:08:32,053 --> 00:08:34,680
Yeah, well, for a cop,
you're a skinny little bitch.

80
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:53,283
Starting now, we have 62 hours.

81
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:56,161
Babylon…

82
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:58,288
took our bait.

83
00:08:59,122 --> 00:09:01,540
From the outside,
this place looks exactly like

84
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,418
every other run-of-the-mill rice factory.

85
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,338
One of the buildings even operates
as a rice warehouse.

86
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:09,132
But it's just a cover.

87
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:14,054
A full one-kilometer radius spanning
all directions is completely flat land.

88
00:09:15,138 --> 00:09:17,515
Anyone approaching
will be spotted immediately.

89
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:19,851
This place is a fortress.

90
00:09:32,614 --> 00:09:34,698
The assholes have upgraded.

91
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:36,618
Now we have to get around all of that.

92
00:09:39,746 --> 00:09:43,373
Most of Babylon's facilities
are installed on their basement floors.

93
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:45,000
The armory is on basement four.

94
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:47,336
The situation room, basement two.

95
00:09:47,337 --> 00:09:49,714
There's a 30-millimeter AA gun
on the rooftop.

96
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:53,050
Ninety-six soldiers
of Babylon's mobile force

97
00:09:53,051 --> 00:09:54,551
are active until 6:00 p.m.

98
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:58,223
But, Jinman, it's supposed
to be a surprise, isn't it?

99
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:01,476
It would be better
to kill Bale somewhere else.

100
00:10:05,188 --> 00:10:06,231
This is the target.

101
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:09,525
The server?

102
00:10:09,526 --> 00:10:12,236
It houses all
of Babylon's classified files.

103
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:14,905
They've been around
since the military dictatorship.

104
00:10:14,906 --> 00:10:17,324
Babylon's carried out
all the intelligence operations,

105
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:19,201
kidnappings, and assassinations

106
00:10:19,202 --> 00:10:20,911
on behalf of every changing regime.

107
00:10:20,912 --> 00:10:23,790
Including selling North Korea weapons
behind our government's back.

108
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:27,251
In the conflict zones
of Southeast and Central Asia,

109
00:10:27,252 --> 00:10:30,295
they made arms deals
with both rebels and government forces.

110
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:33,006
Political coups were engineered
for their own gain.

111
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:34,174
Decades of client lists,

112
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:35,592
intelligence operatives,

113
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:37,219
all their contract kill data.

114
00:10:37,220 --> 00:10:38,930
Everything top secret
is being kept in there.

115
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:45,770
Bale killed hundreds of civilians
during operations.

116
00:10:46,938 --> 00:10:48,940
That evidence is buried there as well.

117
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:51,818
This is our bargaining chip.

118
00:10:52,777 --> 00:10:55,696
Babylon will have no choice
but to be kept in check.

119
00:10:55,697 --> 00:10:58,533
The result is a maintained
state of neutrality.

120
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:02,203
If our plan fails…

121
00:11:04,581 --> 00:11:07,709
this exhausting,
useless war will never end for us.

122
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:12,422
Jian deserves to live a full
and peaceful life.

123
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,300
We can't fail.

124
00:11:16,259 --> 00:11:18,386
Jian needs us to protect her
with this shield.

125
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:20,762
Can't we just hack the data?

126
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:22,431
Impossible.

127
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:24,850
In order to keep it secure
and to prevent overheating,

128
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:27,102
they keep it separate
from the general server room

129
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:29,479
and store it independently underwater.

130
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,981
This wall is made of concrete

131
00:11:30,982 --> 00:11:32,691
and serves as the firewall.

132
00:11:33,985 --> 00:11:37,154
Even so, it has to be connected
to somewhere outside, right?

133
00:11:37,155 --> 00:11:39,907
True, but it's still submerged underwater.

134
00:11:40,992 --> 00:11:43,452
Ah, even a Kim Il Sung University elite

135
00:11:43,453 --> 00:11:44,661
is stumped, huh?

136
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:46,664
Collect the reward and report the spy.

137
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:49,875
This asshole's useless.

138
00:11:49,876 --> 00:11:51,419
What do you propose instead?

139
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:53,963
We're removing the whole thing.

140
00:11:54,589 --> 00:11:56,423
At 1500 hours every day,

141
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:59,092
the server is raised
from the water tank for inspection.

142
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:01,179
Great. We'll hack it then.

143
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:04,933
What the hell, how'd this Thai idiot
ever work with Babylon?

144
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,976
You should keep your dumb mouth shut.

145
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:09,186
Watch your step, man.

146
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:32,960
This is our chance.

147
00:12:32,961 --> 00:12:35,004
But we'll only have 20 minutes.

148
00:12:35,797 --> 00:12:39,300
Infiltrating the enemy network
and downloading the data that quickly?

149
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:41,593
It's impossible even for Zuckerberg.

150
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:42,803
Zuck, who… who is that?

151
00:12:42,804 --> 00:12:44,179
Just say hacking, come on.

152
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,430
Thai genius.

153
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:46,723
You're gonna have to be the one

154
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:48,976
that brings the new-model bomb
to my location.

155
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:50,310
Oh, yeah?

156
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:51,395
Why is that?

157
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:52,562
Because you're good.

158
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:54,606
We can't take weapons
inside Babylon,

159
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:56,316
so we'll go through the armory.

160
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:58,902
Team leaders and up
can carry personal sidearms,

161
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:00,904
but they're only allowed
to access the ammo

162
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:02,365
during an active operation.

163
00:13:05,243 --> 00:13:06,952
The armory has what we need.

164
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:08,870
We'll have to raid it for weapons.

165
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:11,623
In the explosive section,
you'll find the E5 bombs,

166
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:14,876
which were specially manufactured
as miniature bunker-busters.

167
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:18,380
With those, we'll blast into the rooms
above and below the server.

168
00:13:18,381 --> 00:13:21,383
I take the bombs
and blast it into the server?

169
00:13:21,384 --> 00:13:25,513
Pasin, you also have to plant a bomb
above the server on the first floor.

170
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,472
That'll be really tough.

171
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:29,225
Why can't you stop complaining?

172
00:13:30,268 --> 00:13:31,518
I have it just as bad.

173
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:32,936
Look over there.

174
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:34,813
It's not always about the big things.

175
00:13:34,814 --> 00:13:37,859
The most physical things
aren't always the toughest.

176
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:41,320
My issue…

177
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:44,907
is figuring out what bait
will reel this guy in.

178
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,875
BEAUTIFUL FEMALE MASSEUSE!!
ALWAYS ON STANDBY!!

179
00:13:54,876 --> 00:13:56,335
PREMIUM-QUALITY MASSAGE
GRAND OPENING SPECIAL!

180
00:14:02,425 --> 00:14:03,468
DELETE MESSAGES

181
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,561
DELETE ALL

182
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:18,190
To defeat your enemies,
you must think like your enemies.

183
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:35,208
THE PROFESSOR HAS SELECTED
TOMORROW'S SURGE STOCK.

184
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:40,378
South Koreans and capitalism.

185
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:42,172
Gets them every time.

186
00:14:48,137 --> 00:14:49,596
KIM JUNGHO
SECURITY TEAM LEADER

187
00:14:54,352 --> 00:14:56,228
That's cool.

188
00:14:56,229 --> 00:14:58,356
KIM JUNGHO
SECURITY TEAM LEADER

189
00:14:59,190 --> 00:15:01,108
Most of Babylon's waste
is handled

190
00:15:01,109 --> 00:15:03,277
at its own incineration facility.

191
00:15:03,778 --> 00:15:07,572
But a designated company collects
the regular trash once a week.

192
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:10,993
This is the only opening we have
to infiltrate, so we need to be ready.

193
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:23,922
WASTE COLLECTION
& TRANSPORT SPECIALISTS 1643-8834

194
00:15:25,216 --> 00:15:26,508
92 MEO 0583

195
00:15:36,227 --> 00:15:37,519
Mm-hmm.

196
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:38,770
You're trash.

197
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:39,814
Thai garbage.

198
00:15:40,815 --> 00:15:42,233
We're trash together.

199
00:15:47,822 --> 00:15:49,156
PARANG ENVIRONMENT

200
00:15:49,157 --> 00:15:51,367
WASTE COLLECTION & TRANSPORT
SPECIALISTS 1643-8834

201
00:15:52,535 --> 00:15:54,162
Once we get through the entrance…

202
00:15:55,329 --> 00:15:57,455
we still have to pass the X-ray.

203
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:00,876
STOP

204
00:16:04,338 --> 00:16:06,506
I'm gonna wrap
a layer of X-ray resistant film

205
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:08,092
inside the trash bins.

206
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:10,510
It's the same expensive film
the Americans use

207
00:16:10,511 --> 00:16:11,970
in their stealth aircrafts.

208
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:13,180
That's right.

209
00:16:13,181 --> 00:16:15,974
Cheolseung here
will hack into Babylon's intranet for us.

210
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,477
He'll secure the CCTVs
located on our route.

211
00:16:20,021 --> 00:16:23,273
Pasin and I will go to the armory

212
00:16:23,274 --> 00:16:26,067
and grab the bombs and the weapons
that we'll need.

213
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:29,447
Pasin will plant the E5 on the first floor
and move to the server room.

214
00:16:30,031 --> 00:16:31,115
That leaves Bale.

215
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:36,328
Bale is mine.

216
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:54,305
Everything about
the replica is perfect.

217
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:57,767
Except there's nothing I can do
about his left eye.

218
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:01,269
You'll have to put on dark sunglasses
or something to hide it.

219
00:17:08,152 --> 00:17:10,946
JEONG JIAN

220
00:17:23,084 --> 00:17:24,668
Hey, it's me, Uncle.

221
00:17:24,669 --> 00:17:26,169
Miss Jeong Jian?

222
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:27,380
Who is this?

223
00:17:27,922 --> 00:17:31,091
This is Sergeant Park Jinwoo
from the Yecheong Police Station.

224
00:17:31,092 --> 00:17:33,218
I was actually just about to call you.

225
00:17:33,219 --> 00:17:34,220
Oh.

226
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:36,264
And why is that?

227
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:40,184
Well, I'm sorry
to have to tell you this.

228
00:17:40,851 --> 00:17:43,646
Uh, Mr. Jeong Jinman has been found dead.

229
00:17:59,328 --> 00:18:00,371
Miss Jeong Jian?

230
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:04,208
Ah.

231
00:18:06,711 --> 00:18:08,253
I'm Sergeant Park Jinwoo.

232
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:09,547
DETECTIVE DIVISION / VIOLENT CRIMES TEAM
2 PARK JINWOO

233
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:11,173
Right.

234
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:14,677
If you're ready.

235
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:35,031
She looked like she was in shock.

236
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:37,073
But she accepted it.

237
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:38,200
Okay.

238
00:18:40,411 --> 00:18:41,786
Good work, Jinwoo.

239
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:42,997
We'll be waiting for you.

240
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:52,757
Keep going. Straight ahead.

241
00:18:53,674 --> 00:18:55,009
How many minutes will it take?

242
00:18:55,509 --> 00:18:56,801
About 47.

243
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:58,720
No. See if you can make it 40.

244
00:18:58,721 --> 00:18:59,722
Copy.

245
00:19:11,192 --> 00:19:12,318
Did Jian buy it?

246
00:19:14,654 --> 00:19:16,280
My funeral's in 48 hours.

247
00:19:18,032 --> 00:19:19,867
It's also when we're mobilizing.

248
00:19:20,785 --> 00:19:22,328
Those Code Reds…

249
00:19:23,079 --> 00:19:24,704
are they trustworthy?

250
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:27,708
Like human nature,
wolves follow their pack leader.

251
00:19:28,751 --> 00:19:30,378
We'll put our trust in Mr. Kim.

252
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:37,009
I'm sorry, Mr. Kim.

253
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:39,387
It's my fault.

254
00:19:40,262 --> 00:19:42,681
I should've taken better care of things.

255
00:19:42,682 --> 00:19:45,768
Well, that's how life is sometimes.

256
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:49,814
I didn't blame you,
not even once, Yonghan.

257
00:19:56,654 --> 00:20:00,950
But you're asking me
to betray Jinman, posthumously.

258
00:20:01,951 --> 00:20:02,952
Is that right?

259
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:05,329
Seongjo's proposal…

260
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,289
You turned him down.

261
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:10,834
I should have come to see you myself.

262
00:20:10,835 --> 00:20:11,836
I'm sorry.

263
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:38,945
A document?

264
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:40,239
It's a contract.

265
00:20:40,781 --> 00:20:42,282
It's my olive branch.

266
00:20:42,283 --> 00:20:43,867
I want you to come work with us.

267
00:20:43,868 --> 00:20:45,869
Supervise our training center.

268
00:20:45,870 --> 00:20:48,372
You'll be able to restore
your damaged reputation.

269
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:51,333
You'll be able to live comfortably
from now on.

270
00:21:40,758 --> 00:21:42,760
MR. KIM
HAS STEPPED OUTSIDE THE FENCE.

271
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:56,774
Pasin and Cheolseung
will infiltrate first.

272
00:21:59,443 --> 00:22:01,904
WASTE COLLECTION &
TRANSPORT SPECIALISTS 1643-8834

273
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:11,163
External vehicles will be directed
to the underground loading dock.

274
00:22:33,686 --> 00:22:36,105
STOP

275
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:46,322
First time here?

276
00:22:46,323 --> 00:22:48,825
Oh, yeah, Seunghoon
was supposed to be on today.

277
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:50,535
But he's out with COVID.

278
00:22:50,536 --> 00:22:52,121
I'm just filling in while he's sick.

279
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:01,504
WASTE COLLECTION 13:30
LEE SEUNGHOON

280
00:23:15,978 --> 00:23:17,312
Look.

281
00:23:42,796 --> 00:23:43,964
Get out.

282
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:46,800
What?

283
00:24:03,025 --> 00:24:05,486
Um, uh… Is something the matter here or?

284
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:07,404
The back.

285
00:24:28,884 --> 00:24:29,885
Open it.

286
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:31,428
Okay.

287
00:24:31,929 --> 00:24:32,930
So…

288
00:24:33,389 --> 00:24:34,932
Uh, the thing is…

289
00:24:35,557 --> 00:24:37,518
This is really…

290
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:43,398
Smelly stuff.

291
00:24:43,399 --> 00:24:45,566
I stopped by the hospital this morning.

292
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:47,277
Argh, the smell of blood. Shit.

293
00:24:47,778 --> 00:24:49,570
Do you want to open all of these?

294
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:51,448
No. No need for all that. You can shut it.

295
00:24:51,949 --> 00:24:54,033
I know.

296
00:24:54,034 --> 00:24:55,159
It's gross.

297
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:57,037
I never get used to the smell either.

298
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:32,823
Help me out of here.

299
00:25:33,323 --> 00:25:35,492
Look at this Thai trashhole.

300
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:49,757
Jeong Jinman's dead, so what's the rush?

301
00:25:50,716 --> 00:25:53,176
- Hey. Seongjo's pissed off, man, hurry up.
-  No, I got it.

302
00:25:53,177 --> 00:25:55,136
Should we buy something sweet on the way?

303
00:25:55,137 --> 00:25:57,055
I don't think we should go empty-handed.

304
00:25:57,056 --> 00:25:58,514
We're moving out!

305
00:25:58,515 --> 00:26:00,183
Moving out, let's go!

306
00:26:03,604 --> 00:26:04,687
Shit.

307
00:26:09,026 --> 00:26:12,071
Captain, the situation
just got complicated.

308
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:39,139
BROTHER THE SEAGULL IS INJURED,
THE EAGLET IS INSIDE IN THE SHOPPING MALL

309
00:26:47,022 --> 00:26:49,525
Kuma's headed to the shopping mall
with his team.

310
00:26:55,989 --> 00:26:58,492
Pasin, you and Jinwoo withdraw.

311
00:26:59,201 --> 00:27:00,285
Cheolseung, stay put.

312
00:27:02,037 --> 00:27:04,498
Well, guess I'm staying here.

313
00:27:10,504 --> 00:27:12,213
Ah, come on.

314
00:27:12,214 --> 00:27:13,423
Just go.

315
00:27:14,883 --> 00:27:16,301
Hey there, spy.

316
00:27:18,762 --> 00:27:20,013
Don't you die.

317
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:20,865
Pasin,

318
00:28:20,866 --> 00:28:22,408
head on over to Jian.

319
00:28:22,409 --> 00:28:25,329
Minhye can't handle Kuma and his team
on her own, so give her a hand.

320
00:28:33,170 --> 00:28:34,212
Jinman.

321
00:28:35,297 --> 00:28:37,507
None of us are gonna be
going to Hell today.

322
00:28:38,508 --> 00:28:41,470
Jian, she's got all of us to protect her.

323
00:29:05,869 --> 00:29:06,994
Captain.

324
00:29:06,995 --> 00:29:09,080
Cheolseung has reached his first position.

325
00:29:43,657 --> 00:29:44,783
Ah, ah.

326
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:49,454
Bale.

327
00:29:50,580 --> 00:29:52,290
You're going to Hell today.

328
00:30:08,765 --> 00:30:10,225
What can I do about that?

329
00:30:13,020 --> 00:30:14,771
You need to just be honest with him.

330
00:30:20,027 --> 00:30:23,195
Bale and Yonghan are located
in the situation room.

331
00:30:23,196 --> 00:30:24,698
Confirmed.

332
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:29,577
Hold on.

333
00:30:29,578 --> 00:30:31,955
If Pasin left,
who's gonna bring me the bomb?

334
00:30:32,789 --> 00:30:34,708
I'm headed over there right now.

335
00:30:35,417 --> 00:30:38,378
Once I confirm I'm in,
move to your second position.

336
00:30:39,296 --> 00:30:40,379
Copy.

337
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:43,800
DANGER SLOWLY

338
00:30:49,389 --> 00:30:50,974
SEGEON RICE MILL

339
00:31:07,324 --> 00:31:08,784
Team Leader, how've you been?

340
00:31:23,673 --> 00:31:25,008
Wait a minute.

341
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:27,676
Why?

342
00:31:27,677 --> 00:31:28,928
That's Team Leader Three.

343
00:31:28,929 --> 00:31:30,888
- And?
- He entered at 0900 hours.

344
00:31:30,889 --> 00:31:33,099
He's back,
but there's no record of him leaving.

345
00:31:33,100 --> 00:31:35,227
This is such a hassle. Shit.

346
00:31:37,145 --> 00:31:38,771
I'm sorry.

347
00:31:38,772 --> 00:31:40,232
Let me just check one thing.

348
00:31:41,066 --> 00:31:42,776
Call whoever was on duty this morning.

349
00:31:58,834 --> 00:32:00,042
Why isn't he picking up?

350
00:32:00,043 --> 00:32:01,044
Damn idiot.

351
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:02,753
Yeah.

352
00:32:02,754 --> 00:32:04,130
Hey, this is the main gate.

353
00:32:04,131 --> 00:32:07,217
Where was Team Leader Three
this morning after about 0900?

354
00:32:09,678 --> 00:32:14,723
Ah, he was… at the firing range
at 1200, I believe.

355
00:32:14,724 --> 00:32:16,393
Got it. Here.

356
00:32:37,414 --> 00:32:40,000
Which firing range did you go to today?

357
00:32:49,342 --> 00:32:50,385
Forget it.

358
00:32:51,553 --> 00:32:52,637
Open the gate.

359
00:32:53,638 --> 00:32:55,723
I'll proceed
with the password verification.

360
00:32:55,724 --> 00:32:58,727
Hey, he's already been through today.

361
00:32:59,936 --> 00:33:01,645
I'm sorry about this. Truly.

362
00:33:01,646 --> 00:33:03,731
Uh, it's protocol, so I have to do it.

363
00:33:03,732 --> 00:33:04,858
Phoenix.

364
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:12,907
Password, password, password.

365
00:33:12,908 --> 00:33:14,074
What is it?

366
00:33:14,075 --> 00:33:15,451
These Babylon assholes.

367
00:33:15,452 --> 00:33:17,120
I've never done this before.

368
00:33:24,044 --> 00:33:26,087
What's the stupid password? Shit.

369
00:33:27,047 --> 00:33:28,923
I told you to open it.

370
00:33:28,924 --> 00:33:30,883
I'm just following the procedure here.

371
00:33:30,884 --> 00:33:32,135
It's all right.

372
00:33:34,888 --> 00:33:35,889
Rifle.

373
00:33:36,765 --> 00:33:37,890
Are we good?

374
00:33:42,395 --> 00:33:43,563
PHOENIX / RIFFLE

375
00:33:46,566 --> 00:33:49,569
That was tougher than clearing mines
on the demarcation line.

376
00:33:52,948 --> 00:33:54,698
I'm moving to my next position.

377
00:34:34,322 --> 00:34:35,656
Okay.

378
00:34:35,657 --> 00:34:37,783
Cheolseung's moved
into his second position.

379
00:34:37,784 --> 00:34:39,076
Standby.

380
00:34:53,174 --> 00:34:54,592
Ten minutes remaining.

381
00:34:55,343 --> 00:34:57,052
Armory CCTVs?

382
00:34:57,053 --> 00:34:58,471
They're no problem.

383
00:34:59,264 --> 00:35:00,515
DANGER

384
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:13,445
I'm returning my gun.

385
00:35:25,665 --> 00:35:28,876
EXPLOSIVE MATERIALS
WARNING EXPLOSIVE MATERIAL

386
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:35,360
It's almost time.
What's going on?

387
00:36:49,666 --> 00:36:51,041
What is it?

388
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:52,710
Someone tell me what's going on.

389
00:37:41,551 --> 00:37:43,553
Now is your only chance.

390
00:38:20,215 --> 00:38:21,216
Uh, Chief?

391
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:24,760
I think we need to check
Team Leader Bale's location.

392
00:38:24,761 --> 00:38:26,094
Why?

393
00:38:26,095 --> 00:38:28,764
I walked past him in the situation room
a few minutes ago,

394
00:38:28,765 --> 00:38:31,642
but then, two minutes later,
I ran into him on a different floor.

395
00:39:22,610 --> 00:39:23,986
Huh?

396
00:39:23,987 --> 00:39:26,197
Team Leader Bale has two cars on site?

397
00:40:04,152 --> 00:40:05,403
The inspection is complete.

398
00:40:18,666 --> 00:40:20,208
I have to go down.

399
00:40:20,209 --> 00:40:21,710
Something weird's going on.

400
00:40:21,711 --> 00:40:23,337
Hey, wait a sec.

401
00:40:23,338 --> 00:40:24,464
What are you going to do?

402
00:41:03,795 --> 00:41:05,338
Ah, shit.

403
00:41:15,223 --> 00:41:17,182
I took care of the first floor.

404
00:41:17,183 --> 00:41:19,936
I was waiting forever,
I thought you died in there.

405
00:41:23,439 --> 00:41:25,191
Glad you're alive.

406
00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:27,359
I won't die today.

407
00:41:29,862 --> 00:41:30,863
Or ever.

408
00:41:33,825 --> 00:41:37,160
Check the route and radius of movement
to see where that vehicle came from,

409
00:41:37,161 --> 00:41:38,662
and run a malware scan.

410
00:41:38,663 --> 00:41:40,581
- We could've been hacked.
- Yes, sir.

411
00:42:22,582 --> 00:42:24,249
Server room installation complete.

412
00:42:24,250 --> 00:42:25,418
Okay.

413
00:42:32,550 --> 00:42:34,343
Ah, shit.

414
00:42:35,303 --> 00:42:36,971
My location's been compromised.

415
00:42:46,397 --> 00:42:47,773
Team two has arrived.

416
00:42:47,774 --> 00:42:48,941
Ten minutes to entry.

417
00:42:49,442 --> 00:42:50,443
General.

418
00:42:51,903 --> 00:42:52,987
Jeong Jinman…

419
00:42:53,863 --> 00:42:55,281
Do you think he's still alive?

420
00:43:04,207 --> 00:43:07,168
Sir, one of the drones has been shot,
and we've been hacked.

421
00:43:10,838 --> 00:43:12,881
What? What's wrong?

422
00:43:20,098 --> 00:43:22,683
Oh, shit. That son of a bitch.

423
00:43:26,729 --> 00:43:28,314
What's going on? Go find out.

424
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:59,947
17 MEO 4396

425
00:46:00,883 --> 00:46:02,176
When I heard you were dead,

426
00:46:03,386 --> 00:46:05,137
I was so disappointed.

427
00:46:21,028 --> 00:46:22,029
What?

428
00:46:23,114 --> 00:46:24,198
You're not scared?

429
00:47:35,019 --> 00:47:36,020
See you later.

430
00:48:44,338 --> 00:48:45,464
Jinman!

431
00:48:47,007 --> 00:48:48,342
It's over.

432
00:48:49,885 --> 00:48:51,511
It's time to end this.

433
00:49:31,594 --> 00:49:33,512
Shoot him down, idiots!

434
00:50:53,175 --> 00:50:54,425
It's dangerous out here.

435
00:50:54,426 --> 00:50:56,928
You should go back inside
and wait in the shopping mall.

436
00:50:56,929 --> 00:50:59,640
Sir. Someone is heading
this way right now.

437
00:51:01,809 --> 00:51:03,143
You just stay here.

438
00:51:03,978 --> 00:51:04,979
It's all right.

439
00:51:16,240 --> 00:51:17,575
Are they one of ours?

440
00:51:18,826 --> 00:51:21,078
No, sir, they haven't been confirmed.

441
00:51:33,007 --> 00:51:35,384
Jinman, we're almost there.

442
00:52:06,498 --> 00:52:07,958
I know that man.

443
00:53:10,771 --> 00:53:15,608
A SHOP FOR KILLERS 2

444
00:53:38,716 --> 00:53:41,635
SIGMA

445
00:53:47,808 --> 00:53:49,392
- Yeah?
-  Onee-chan,

446
00:53:49,393 --> 00:53:51,853
you're too old to be playing
around in clubs.

447
00:53:51,854 --> 00:53:53,354
I'm not playing.

448
00:53:53,355 --> 00:53:54,897
I'm working.

449
00:53:54,898 --> 00:53:56,274
How'd you get in?

450
00:53:56,275 --> 00:53:59,694
Security must be slacking,
they let anyone in these days.

451
00:53:59,695 --> 00:54:01,362
You've got to be joking.

452
00:54:01,363 --> 00:54:04,240
I can get in wherever I want.

453
00:54:04,241 --> 00:54:06,076
Yeah, you wish.

454
00:54:07,953 --> 00:54:10,037
I'm working, stop interfering.

455
00:54:10,038 --> 00:54:11,330
What is it that you want?

456
00:54:11,331 --> 00:54:13,041
The director is summoning you.

457
00:54:14,042 --> 00:54:16,253
What, why?

458
00:54:17,254 --> 00:54:19,172
Jeong Jinman.

459
00:54:19,173 --> 00:54:20,257
Do you remember him?

460
00:54:24,136 --> 00:54:25,262
I remember.
